awhile back I was told, by th writer of this piece, that David Crosby was sent a link to Sebadoh’s version of his ‘everybody’s been burned’ .. the idea terrified me because I had come t figure my cover wasn’t v good.. ear infections and earplugs -really- don’t mix so I will doing the thing I thought I’d never do: wear these bad boys during a show.. I prob can’t do much head banging , unfortunately.. lame all around : / .. thanks to our tour manager @dan.mapp.1 for driving all over LA t find the crucial -30db variety ear muffs..

I thought I’d be able to wear these protective muffs onstage and let my ears heal without jamming earplugs into their infected depths for 2 hours a day..I was wrong.. I -have- to move when I play, and the muffs slide off my mop, plus the music sounds like muddled garbage with them on.. so, back to the solid -30db plugs and wax-cover for th good time rockin’ vibe ..thankfully the Augmentin has worked well enough that these last two shows here in lo-cal (woo!) haven’t made it worse...in fact, the show in Santa Ana put me way down the road t recovery, amazing crowd!

social_posts.post_text: bangers, doll and I are in Hyannis for a memorial service (on a whale watch!) for a friend’s mom.. got here a little early t dodge th weekend traffic.. it’s like the gritty Massachusetts I know but with ferries and amazing seafood..

today we experienced an amazing memorial service for a friend’s mom who was an avid whale watcher and nature photographer..they laid her t rest in th ocean off Cape Cod while humpback whales breached the surface on both sides of the boat..I took this pic shortly after, two whales diving in synch w a third on the left.. humpbacks don’t swim as a family pod, they choose friends they like to hunt with.. and some of them swim alone.. thanks t @instacais and @debengram for sharing this extraordinary day with us

can’t believe it, I got a replacement/back-up for my trusty KORG Bass-Synthe.. I’ve used my sweet baby (lower part of foto) on almost every LP I’ve made for the last 25 years (esp folk implosion and solo) yes, she’s even found her way on to a Dinosaur Jr record.. it’s been the most versatile, magical instrument I’ve ever known.. she started sounding sick a few years ago, her tuning fluctuating now and again.. it’s gotten worse.. I looked into replacing her but was looking at paying about 20-30x her original price (I got her for $100) …I tried a few new keyboards but nothing came close to recreating her warm and otherworldly tone.. NOTHING.. then, via a Reverb link from @jmpizzoferrato that he himself was considering having experienced her magic firsthand, I swooped in and snagged a partner for my baby at only 8x the original price!! the ‘new’ one is definitely older so I don’t know how long he’ll last..as you can see I really put her to work, festooned her w stickers, took her to Australia (almost had a wicked fight w a stewardess who wanted me to gate check her).. honestly it’s a miracle she lasted as long as she did and if I can find a synth doctor she’ll be back..in the meantime wish me luck with my new old man.. this model of synth held down the low-end for the B-52s and the high octaves are like a 70s horror film..it’s all in the ‘traveler’ bar .. tnx t the universe (and Justin) for more beautiful timing.. this tape turned 40 this week (dated 9/12/83) it’s a compilation (no one was calling them mix-tapes back then) for my friend Mark Harris. He passed away this summer and his ex-wife just sent me some of the tapes he had saved..here’s the story:
starting in ‘81 I regularly sent Mark the exciting music I was discovering..at first Circle Jerks, Black Flag etc.. mainly hardcore with some U.K. post-punk in there..this tape marks a transition in the musical landscape w/ the inclusion of REM.. it was the last tape I sent that featured hardcore or my own songs..J Mascis was a freshman at th University of Massachusetts, our band Deep Wound would dissolve and mutate into Dinosaur by mid-84 .. instead of playing disc jockey on the tape and announcing all of the songs (like I did on my first tapes for Mark) I began making collages of song-fragments and found sounds to fill the gaps.. I had found the right combination of Radio Shack adapters and portable tape recorders to create the kind of slurry that characterized Poledo on Dinosaur’s second L.P. ..
